-- Serb Telekom May Use 2012 Income for Investments, Novosti Says
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2013-05-29T07:30:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-29/serb-telekom-may-use-2012-income-for-investments-novosti-says.html
Telekom Srbija AD, Serbia’s state-controlled phone company, wants to spend last year’s earnings on
upgrades rather than dividends to shareholders,  Vecernje Novosti 
newspaper reported, citing a company source it didn’t name.  Shareholders will vote on June 27 on 2013 investments that
may be worth 200 million euros ($257 million), it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
